What is MongoDB?
-----------------

* MongoDB is a Document Oriented Database
* Open Source
* High Performance
* Horizontally Scalable (Web Scale, Sharding)
* Full Featured (buzzword compilance!)

MongoDB is a good choice if you have a lot of data that you want to get at quickly.

Library - a demo application
-----------------------------

* Users
* Books
* Authors
* Publishers

Download
---------

* [MongoDB - the database](http://www.mongodb.org/)
* [Mojolicious::Lite](https://metacpan.org/pod/Mojolicious::Lite)
* [MongoDB - Perl client](https://metacpan.org/pod/MongoDB)

Inside the MongoDB Perl client

* [MongoDB::Client](https://metacpan.org/pod/MongoDB::Client) - Encapsulates connection and server info
* [MongoDB::Database](https://metacpan.org/pod/MongoDB::Database) - Represents a database (namespace) on the MongoDB server
* [MongoDB::Collection](https://metacpan.org/pod/MongoDB::Collection) - Represents a collection (table? kinda) in a database
* [MongoDB::Cursor](https://metacpan.org/pod/MongoDB::Cursor) - Retreives documents (rows? kinda) from a collection



